## Project Structure

This project is organized to separate your hardware logic from your machine learning training pipeline.

* **`src/`**: Contains the core logic. 
    * `main.cpp`: The main state-machine implementation, I2C bare-metal communication, and TFLite inference loop.
* **`include/`**: Contains shared header files.
    * `model.h`: The header file containing your TensorFlow Lite model array, pre-compiled for the ESP32-S3.
* **`tools/`**: Contains the Python pipeline used to create the "brain" of the lock.
    * `Neural_training.ipynb`: The training script.
    * `data_collector.py`: The script used to gather sensor data.
    * `sensor_data_preprocessing.ipynb`: The code that cleaned the raw CSV data into the format the AI understands.
* **`platformio.ini`**: The hardware configuration file, defining memory partitions and build flags for the ESP32-S3 N16R8.
* **`*.csv`**: Raw datasets used during the training phase.